   Help and FAQ

   Problems with this Website?

   How do I access the digital edition of Science News?

   Subscribers have full online access to the early digital edition of the current print magazine. You must have verified your subscription by logging into our website and entering your subscriber
   number into your profile. Once you have done that, from the SN home page, click on the Digital Edition link under the image of the magazine cover.

   How do I access an article that's more than one year old?

   Anyone can read articles published in the last 12 months for free on www.sciencenews.org. But only subscribers can access articles published more than a year ago. The Science News online
   archive contains all the content from the print editions from 2000 to the present.  You must have verified your subscription by logging into our website and entering your subscriber number into
   your profile.
   Other issues with the site?
   We apologize for any difficulty you may be having. Email us at scinews@sciencenews.org
   About Science News
   How often does Science News publish?

   Science News publishes our print magazine biweekly on Saturdays, with our digital edition available to paid subscribers via password. Our website is updated weekdays with breaking science news
   and our e-mail headline service is available daily.

   Who publishes Science News?

   Science News is published by Society for Science & the Public (SSP), a nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization located in Washington, D.C., dedicated to the public engagement in scientific research
   and education. SSP educates and informs students, parents, teachers and the greater community about the evolving and influential world of science.

